    • parseList

      public static ArrayList<String> parseList(String value) throws Exception
      Parse a list of values.

      If there's no need to parse a value containing a representation of a list or tuple, each value should have the prefix #NOPARSE#

      Examples: * Simple type - "value1" or "2011-09-20T20:33:01.386+01:00" or "true" * Tuple - "{value1; 100; 2011-09-20T20:33:01.386+01:00}" * List - "(value1; value2; {value1; 100; 2011-09-20T20:33:01.386+01:00})" * No parse - "#NOPARSE#{value1; 100; 2011-09-20T20:33:01.386+01:00}"

      Parameters:
      value - String content
      Returns:
      the elements list
      Throws:
      Exception

    • parseTuple

      public static ArrayList<String> parseTuple(String value) throws Exception
      Parse a tuple of values.
